    "description": "Tsubaki Nakashima Co., Ltd. manufactures and sells industrial precision balls, rollers, blowers, and medical equipment and hygiene equipment in Japan and internationally. The company operates through Precision Components Business and Bloor Real Estate Business segments. It offers precision steel balls, including bearing and stainless steel, ballpoint pen, and various metal balls for use in home electronics, such as air conditioners, refrigerators, and vacuum cleaners; and precision tapered, spherical, cylindrical, and needle rollers. The company also provides precision ceramic balls, including silicon nitride and alumina oxide balls for use in wind power generators, electric vehicles, and semiconductor manufacturing equipment applications. In addition, it offers medical and metrology products. Further, the company provides iron and steel, electric power, wind tunnel, and other blowers for steel, thermal power, nuclear power, biomass power, and other applications; and customized solutions comprising solid plastic balls, specially manufactured products, and glass balls for medical diagnostic tests and devices. Additionally, it is involved in real estate leasing. Tsubaki Nakashima Co., Ltd. was founded in 1934 and is headquartered in Osaka, Japan."
